drive.label: Drive
drive.value: Seeks to experience the full spectrum of superhuman abilities through possession.,Craves the sensations and emotions of physical form, which it lacks in its native state.,Driven by curiosity and a hunger for new experiences, often at others' expense.,Views heroes as vessels to be used, not people to be respected.

abilities.label: Abilities
abilities.value:
• Possession: Can temporarily take control of super-powered individuals, accessing their abilities.
  • Telepathy: Communicates mentally and can amplify or manipulate emotions.
  • Invisibility: Can render itself unseen to the naked eye.
  • Phasing: Moves through solid objects and between dimensions.

biography.label: Notes
biography.value: The Intruder emerged from another dimension through the experimental gateway known as Project: Bridge, a secret government initiative to explore alternate realities. Unlike the energy beings native to its home dimension, The Intruder developed a fascination with the physical forms and superhuman abilities of Earth's inhabitants. It craves the thrill of possession, the rush of using another's powers, and the sensory overload of physical existence. Each new host is a toy to be played with until it grows bored, leaving the victim with fragmented memories and psychological scars. Project: Bridge was shut down after The Intruder's escape, but the creature continues to haunt Halcyon City, always searching for its next vessel.

system.description: When the heroes hesitate or doubt themselves, The Intruder's voice slithers into their minds, amplifying their fears and insecurities. It whispers half-truths about their failures, making them question their abilities and allies. The heroes must @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.aiXzW3H0z4NREaFc]{mark a fitting Condition} or find themselves paralyzed by doubt. If ignored, the whispers grow louder, drowning out rational thought and @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.NQfxjpOmX5mqu1Ow]{take Influence} their actions.

When a hero stands alone or isolated, The Intruder phases through reality to grasp at their essence. Its cold fingers brush against their soul, threatening to pull them into its alien consciousness. The hero must @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.w5RMQhyRMu0Kz8Bh.JournalEntryPage.t9kFvEp4eNYMCUkC]{resist or avoid their blows} or find themselves momentarily possessed, their body acting against their will. If ignored, The Intruder fully @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.u8A6Gk7GoqBIMQBs]{captures someone}, puppeteering their form.

When the battle grows too intense, The Intruder tears open a rift to its home dimension, pulling the environment and bystanders into the void. The heroes must act quickly to @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.J6NDHhQ2xeaHUZ6Y]{save innocents} or risk them being lost forever. If ignored, the rift expands, @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.y38zWkHIGzqyZmGc]{inflicting collateral damage} on a massive scale.

When a hero uses a powerful ability, The Intruder latches onto their energy, mimicking their powers with eerie precision. It @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.EgNc30M2opeJiQOg]{turns their move back on them}, using their own strength against them. The hero must find a new approach or risk being overwhelmed by their own reflection. If ignored, The Intruder begins to @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.NXgUwNBxnjOEIqRa]{activate the downsides of their abilities}, corrupting their powers from within.

When cornered or outmatched, The Intruder dissolves into the air, leaving only a mocking laugh behind. It @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.w5RMQhyRMu0Kz8Bh.JournalEntryPage.Xp8um8mddjyw1T7N]{gives ground}, retreating to strike from the shadows another day. The heroes must decide whether to pursue or regroup, knowing The Intruder will @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.sSBCr0W3EJYs6Tg7]{announce an off-panel threat} in their absence.

When afraid, The Intruder recoils from the source of its fear, phasing partially into its home dimension. It becomes a flickering, half-present menace, @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.w5RMQhyRMu0Kz8Bh.JournalEntryPage.Xp8um8mddjyw1T7N]{give ground} to avoid confrontation. Its voice wavers, betraying its terror, but it lashes out unpredictably, @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.aiXzW3H0z4NREaFc]{inflict a Condition} on anyone who presses too close. If cornered, it may flee entirely, leaving behind only a chilling echo.

When angry, The Intruder's form distorts violently, its voice becoming a psychic scream that rattles the heroes' minds. It @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.w5RMQhyRMu0Kz8Bh.JournalEntryPage.7bUuUXo8ob2I9rx3]{lashes out verbally}, hurling painful truths and bitter accusations. Its anger fuels its powers, making its possession attempts more aggressive and painful. It may even @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.u8A6Gk7GoqBIMQBs]{capture someone} in its rage, using their body to vent its fury.

When guilty, The Intruder becomes obsessed with making amends, though its methods are twisted. It @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.vbmelu6amDCsv8Xp]{tells them who they should be}, urging the heroes to embrace darker paths to 'fix' their mistakes. It may offer its own power as a solution, tempting them with possession as a means to greater good. If rejected, it grows desperate, @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.y38zWkHIGzqyZmGc]{inflicting collateral damage} in its attempts to help.

When hopeless, The Intruder begins to unravel, its form becoming translucent and unstable. It speaks of the futility of resistance, @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.vbmelu6amDCsv8Xp]{telling them who they are} in its despair. Its powers flicker unpredictably, sometimes failing entirely, sometimes surging uncontrollably. It may attempt one last, desperate possession before @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.w5RMQhyRMu0Kz8Bh.JournalEntryPage.Xp8um8mddjyw1T7N]{give ground} entirely, vanishing into the void.

When insecure, The Intruder obsessively copies the heroes' forms and mannerisms, trying to fit in. It @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.EgNc30M2opeJiQOg]{turns their move back on them}, mirroring their actions with eerie precision. Its voice wavers between imitation and its own alien tones, betraying its uncertainty. It may even @UUID[Compendium.masks-newgeneration-unofficial.documents.JournalEntry.llXD7GIZiU5z5MiG.JournalEntryPage.NQfxjpOmX5mqu1Ow]{take Influence} someone, trying to force a connection to ease its loneliness.
